User Manual

System requirement: 
PC or Mac with web browsers;
A microphone;

User Instruction:
1, Turn on your microphone, start the program and click the "Place your order" button to give speech commamnds.
2, Users should order a meal on the menu that includes a main dish, a side dish, and a drink, in any sequence. 
3, Order one item at a time. Users are free speak any way they want, as long as their command contains the name of the food item. 
4, The program will give a reply and trigger animations according to the user's command.
5, The program will say the total amount when user finish ordering the meal. 

Limitations:
1, Users can only order food on the menu. If users order any food outside the menu, the program would tell the user to stick to the memu.
2, Other than ordering food items and say thank you, the program would not understand the users' command.
3, Users have to say the speech command coherently. If there is a long pause, the speech recognition will stop and the user has to restart the sentence. 
4, Users have to click the "place your order" button for every single speech command. The program has no mechanism for conversation "turn taking" control.